{
  "text": "The three types of genomic association each contain quantitative information (e.g. the number of times two genes occur together in an operon). Additionally, there is a positive correlation between the genomic associations and the likelihood and strength of interactions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ; this allows the derivation of a scoring system.",
  "correct_citation": {
